caption: I only ordered a salad and smoothie to go. The smoothie was made very quickly but my salad took about 35 mins to cook. I got the Mediterranean without cheese and added avocado & scrambled tofu. It had plenty of veggie topping & tasted good. The smoothie was completely runny by the time I got my salad & didn’t have a lot of flavor. The people working were very nice though.
Home style feeling food they really cooking from scratch so really loved it. Recommend 💯 %
I love this place!! Unfortunately I moved to Ft Lauderdale so i can’t eat here regularly. I wish you had more locations. Please open something up here!

Our first experience, we were out looking for something different to eat.. We came across KC so we dropped in.. We looked at the menu and immediately asked to speak to the chef.. Chef Dominique came to our table and made us feel right at home. We asked what he'd suggest and we tried about 6 different dishes and they were all excellent. He is very personable. He cooked the food and came back to see that everything was to our liking. He actually stayed and had a conversation with us. Excellent food, atmosphere and service.. I highly recommend you drop in. You will not be disappointed.
best healthy food in town and a great atmosphere
Great live Jazz music.  Amazing atmosphere and great way to spend a Sunday afternoon!
The cuisine is delicious...I’m vegan and I love the organic buckwheat soba noodles. The owner is so personable with excellent customer service. I will definitely come back!!!

This place is pretty but nothing more. One of their chairs broke the second one of us sat down on it. While we were luckily not to be seriously injured, and while a broken chair could happen at many places, it was the reaction of the staff that was so appalling.
Amazing food. Extended vegan and vegetarian options. Awesome staff. Caring and absolutely delicious. Food made with love. Thank you ❤️ A must to eat here if going around the area.
Chef Dominique and his staff are extremely professional and polite.  The menu has something for everyone.  I enjoyed the veggie burger with the cashew cheese.  Looking forward to returning.
I was given soup joumou while I was waiting for my order. It really warmed my heart because it's a important dish in my culture. Will definitely be coming back!!
Great food. I ordered delivery and did not wait long at all. Very flavorful and fresh

This is a hidden gem with an amazing menu, that is fully customizable for all dietary needs and restrictions. Not only is the food delicious and prepared with love and care, but it's also healthy and wholesome.

For serving a wonderful meal, I wanted to thank the restaurant! I have been helped by your snacks, and I'm always running. Fantastic treats! The meals served are delicious. I fell in love with nourishment! I can't wait to try Amazing Foods again!! Yeah, thanks!!!

This is an amazing restaurant with healthy and delicious food. The chef is the owner and he almost always there and has great positive energy. I'd recommend this place to anyone. It's a little hard to find because it's in the lobby of an office building but well worth finding because it's a hidden gem.
Great food!

I am so happy to have found KC Healthy Cooking. It was a pleasure meeting Chef Dominique. Our lunch was a sample of the recommended dishes- pumpkin soup, buckwheat noodles and Djon djon rice. All incredibly fresh with excellent flavors. I don’t often write reviews, but truly feel they have something special here in Miami. Thanks for a great lunch!
Wow, such great vegan food! Just loved it! 😊
I love going to this restaurant when ever I'm on the area. The food is amazing the menu has a Variety healthy food to choose from I can never get tired of the what's on the menu.

I regret not discovering this gem sooner. It's location is a little hidden but nevertheless, this place is worth a visit. Dominique, the owner is really nice and hospitable. He sat and chatted with me as I ate my lunch. I had the breadfruit with legume...sooooo tasty. The soup joumou is super thick and the smoothies are fresh. Will be back soon !

The food was delicious. Very fresh, like homemade cooking. I will definitely recommend the djon djon flavored rice. I had the salmon with a spicy tomato sauce, YUMMY! Great customer service. The young lady at the register was very nice and accommodating. This is definitely my new go to restaurant whenever I’m in town!!! I’m recommending this place to everyone😅
Great food with very friendly staff. Tried the buckwheat noodles and pumpkin soup. Both were addictive -- savory and delicious. Big fan and will definitely be back!
Good food and service. A1

Delicious, fresh, healthy. Quality (every single time) and quantity (good portions). Friendly service. Difficult to find from the street but well worth it once you do. Fantastic smoothies and shakes. 10/10

Hard to see from the main street but it’s a little slice of paradise between 2 big commercial buildings.  AMAZING food! I blown away by the lox bagel and the pumpkin soup! Loved the outdoor seating area with cute gardening and colorful vibes.  The Owner Dominique is so friendly and puts lots of love into everything. Our waitress Mo, was so sweet.  Highly recommend this place and will plan to stop by anytime I come to Miami for work.

I just popped in to have breakfast, had trouble finding it, BUT IT WAS WORTH THE EFFORT. My breakfast was off the menu, a creation of granola, walnuts, honey , cinnamon, blueberries and strawberries sitting on a sea of a smooth cashew,  almond, spinach blend. NICE!!
This place is really a gem. Great healthy food with a Haitian twist.

Can’t say enough about the amazing flavors, quality ingredients and hospitality of the owner and staff!  Worth a visit!!!
Great food and family friendly! I am never dissatisfied with Chef Dominques menu and he is making new dishes everyday!
Little cafe on the side of the 11900 building. Best little cafe I have been to in a long while. Very interactive and lively. Can't wait to come back, all of their recommendations have been amazing.
Very good food, chill atmosphere. It’s in an office building on the first floor. Great service, too- Matt was very nice.
I like it
The stuffed avocado is my main go to!
Best cooked food in the area. Period 😬

This place is brilliant.   While they have a broad menu - it is still hinged by some outstanding Vegan dishes.   The Buckwheat noodles with mushrooms is outstanding, the portabello black bean burger is to die for - and in case you even think about missing it:  make sure you have the Vegan Banana Bread (warmed).  Plus, do not miss the entertainment - they have a gal doing a great job on the piano with here beautiful voice singing to add to the overall enjoyment of the meal.

Hidden in an office building opposite Home Depot, this place has remained busy day and evenings, popular with many regulars due to its copious, affordable, healthy food.   Run by a gracious Haitian American and with piano/song provided by his wife on some days, there is also very fast Internet, an outdoor terrace and free covered parking in the rear.
❤️Selection of healthy food is huge. Taste of every dish super special and delicious. Customer service very nice and helpful. I wish I could put more then 5 stars. Highly Recommend ❤️
The meal plans are amazing  at this  place. The food is Healthy and full of amazing flavors.
Fantástico. I love their good. It Is delicious!!!

KC's is located on Biscayne Blvd. adjacent to the big 11900 Biscayne Blvd building. Placards direct you to it's walkway or you might miss it. It is it's sixth year at this location, so business must be good, and as a first-timer myself, I can see why. They have a lot of vegan friendly dishes, and keep the meats at chicken, fish, and turkey breast. You will be greated and personally served by Chef Dominique, a very engaging person that you can tell is passionate about what he does. The food came out in a very reasonable time and was excellent. If you love Banana Bread, ask the Chef to put it aside for you because it goes fast. Prices are very reasonable and the atmosphere is pleasant. Meal plans are also available. Be sure to check it out!
Amazing food and the owner is an absolute joy
Excellent everything food and services!
Great food and friendly staff
Great food and service.
Food is delicious each time we've eaten here. The service is excellent as well!

I was so disappointed I wanted to try them out for the first time today I ordered large fresh squeezed juice of the day they delivered me small one I paid extra money for large one and after sitting for 30 minutes it was nothing but water and some powder definitely no vegetables in this blend. The salmon was not bad the portion was just too small definitely not worth 27 dollars for this order.
I had the salmon and sautéed vegetables which was cooked in coconut oil. It was delicious!!!!! Very good customer service.
THE BEST hidden secret!  Great food, great customer service.. You must go!
Always enjoy myself when I go to KC. Food is always fresh and love the vegan spin on my favorite Haitian dishes.
Love this place!!!!!!!! Come here all the time because of Matt and chef!! Great people that means great food. Definitely the place to eat!!!!

Food amazing,chief amazing ,staff amazing and the buck wheat noodle 5 stars amazing

Great food with fresh and healthy ingredients is served here. The pumpkin soup was to die for and the Latina flatbread was as delicious as it was artful. It was a pleasure to enjoy lunch in this casual, arty and relaxed atmosphere. Owner/chef makes everyone feel welcomed. If you are lucky, Daphne may stop by and sing a few tunes.

Always love it here. Chef Dominique and everyone here is so helpful and kind. The food is well priced, wholesome, fresh and most importantly  NUTRITIOUS. It's somewhat hidden inside an office building but don't be fooled. This place is the bomb. Vegan and veggie friendly too. Chicken and other choices also available.
Every dish was delicious.

This place was a bit hidden but let me tell you that it's worth the find.  Top chef Dominique was more than helpful and friendly. Went to all tables and even let us sample some of the food that he had.  Absolutely loved the experience here and food. Will be coming back next time I'm in Miami!

Nutritious and delicious food for the mind, body, and spirit! I am so happy to have found this gem located discretely on the ground level of Mercantile bank... My partner and I enjoyed the Pumpkin Joumou Soup and Buckwheat Soba Noodles, followed by the soft, moist, and decadent banana bread for dessert. Glenda, Matt, and the wonderful cooks in the back were also an intrinsic part of our amazing experience. I appreciate the entire staffs lively customer service and the uplifting atmosphere they have created. I would recommend this beautiful and humble spot to all types of people; vegans, vegetarians, and omnivores alike, this place has something for you! Thank you KC Healthy Cooking, we love you and are so happy to support your small, yet mighty business!

Awesome awesome awesome! Finally got to eat here after hearing about it for a while...the food was delicious. Chef Jerry is so welcoming and the care he puts into the food can be tasted. There are so many healthy options on the menu it's hard to decide what to eat! (Make sure you try the pumpkin soup though.) Prices are fantastic for Miami eating, and you'll leave stuffed. If you are vegan or vegetarian, skip the whole foods salad bar and eat at KC instead!

Matt is the best here. He knows his ingredients for every item on the menu. He’s very kind and gives the best service ever. This healthy food restaurant is a little gem. There’s an outside patio and nicely decorated inside. I’ve come twice now and will continue. I just simply feel at home here. The food here is so tasty and fresh! I just love this place and the food. Thank you kc healthy cooking. Best of luck From Julie
The food is amazingly delicious and the staff are very friendly. The atmosphere is awesome, i highly recommend this place to eat a healthy meal.😊

Simply amazing, healthy, and nutritious food. Also, the customer service is the best. This place is a hidden jewel.

The service is impeccable. The food was so delicious. They are vegan friendly. They have a pumkin soup (joumou) to die for. This is a must go to restaurant. When I thought things couldn't get any better, I was offered the dessert (vegan) was the icing on the cake. Ohhh how can I forget the soursop juice! Omg!!! Delicious!
Welcoming staff, great tasting food, and a generous friendly chef. Thank you fornyour smile.

Wonderful staff. Got a free sample of delicious pumpkin lentil soup. My jerk chicken wrap was excellent with fresh ingredients.

Great first time experience for lunch. Server was very friendly and funny. Chef Dominique has great interaction with us also. But the food was what we really came for and we weren't disappointed. Haitian Vegan options for a Miami born Haitian where I don't have to lose out on the flavors to make up for a healthy choice. Highly recommended.

This is one of the best dinning experiences I have ever had in Miami! The food is ALWAYS worth the wait. I have driven from Kendall numerous times just to have a delicious and gracious meal here. They are always busy and I see why, the restaurant is truly a GEM. Everyone must go!

Our first time lunch and it won't be the last.  The tuna wrap was fresh and delicious.  My husband had the chicken salad with avocado also fresh an delicious. Friendly service.
Awesome experience!  Loved the healthy food but the employees were just as good.  I will definitely eat here every time I am in the area.  Did I mention the great food?  Oh, I did.

Great attentive service. Matt gave a recommendation without having to ask for one. I was given a complimentary Joumou (Pumpkin) soup. Very warm and tasty! Thank you KC for staying true to great service and warm welcome. I will be coming here again 👍
